#"The Forbidden Seas"
"The Forbidden Seas" celebrates my 2
first years in cryptoart, a time of
unknown, experimentation, and
discovery. A time when everyone
rolled their eyes at us and thought we
had lost our shit. How things have
changed... Quotes from Herman
Melville´s Moby-Dick. I thought they
were a good representation of my
state of mind at the time. One of the
first of many musical collabs with my
mate, the talented DARK KóLOR

#"Classic Skulls"
Acrylic paintings of  skulls on rough linen canvas contrasting hot and cold colors.  "Skeenee´s Classics" series, traditional paintings on canvas tokenized on the Ethereum blockchain.

#"Minimalist Skulls"
Skeenee´s Minimalist Skull series showcases a series of skulls stripped down to their essential curves & shapes painted with a limited color scheme(3 colors) without gradients or shading techniques. 5 variations of different colors are available for each skull.

#"Because Aliens"
Created for my good friends at MarbleCards / Meme.com.

Puny humans devoid of intelligence and ingenuity, your alien overlords are responsible for every single one of your advancements. Without them you would still be eating mud. “Because Aliens” is Skeenee´s first piece of Meme Art depicting Giorgio Skullito, the star of the famed “history” channel show Ancient Aliens.

#SKEENEE

Cryptoart OG 2019 | Skeleton Re-Animator | Middle Finger Painter | Metaverse Pioneer | Art Pyromaniac  

"Madrid based Belgian artist obsessed with skulls and anatomy in general. Creation is my passion. Art is a research. Instead of merely copying reality, my focus is to understand what lies behind it, to see past the details and find the essence of things. Every curve has a life, a reason to be, a beginning and an end, a personality."
